State Oil Co. of Azerbaijan has been
approached by  BP Plc (BP/)  over exploring a shallow section of the
Absheron shelf in the  Caspian Sea , Trend said today, citing
Xosbaxt Yusifzada, the Azeri producerâ€™s first vice president.  Socar, as the Baku-based company is known, is considering
the proposal, Yusifzada said, according to the news service.  Tamam Bayatli, a BP spokeswoman in the Azeri capital, said
the company is interested in further oil and gas exploration in
Azerbaijan, declining to elaborate. Yusifzada said Azerbaijan
has 2 billion metric tons of proved reserves of oil and 2.55
trillion cubic meters of gas, according to Trend.  To contact the reporter on this story:
